      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I strongly advise against double-dosing on Zyrtec, as this can increase the risk of side effects and interactions with other medications. Excessive use of antihistamines can cause drowsiness, dizziness, and stomach problems. It's recommended to take the recommended dose of one tablet once a day, as instructed on the packaging, rather than trying to self-medicate with extra doses. Trying to force yourself to fall asleep on the prescribed dose may still cause discomfort and isn't a long-term solution.",
